Use Directory parameter
* SAVEDIR :SAVEDIR 
Save Directory parameter
* FILE    :FILE    
File name parameter
* HELP    :HELP    
Help file parameter
* DEFAULT :DEFAULT 
Default prefs parameter
* GUI     :GUI     
Gui definition parameter
* PORTNAME:PORTNAME
ARexx portname parameter
@end menu

@node DIR
@unnumberedsec DIR parameter
@cindex DIR parameter

This specifies the name of the directory where the prefs file
should be saved when the 'Use' gadget is clicked.

It should end with : or /.

@node SAVEDIR
@unnumberedsec SAVEDIR parameter
@cindex SAVEDIR parameter

This specifies the name of the directory where the prefs file
should be saved when the 'Save' gadget is clicked.

It should end with : or /.

@node FILE
@unnumberedsec FILE parameter
@cindex FILE parameter

This specifies the name of the file to save the prefs in
when the 'Use' or 'Save' gadget is clicked.

@node HELP
@unnumberedsec HELP parameter
@cindex HELP parameter

This specifies the name of the AmigaGuide file from
which help will be displayed when the Help key is pressed.

@node DEFAULT
@unnumberedsec DEFAULT parameter
@cindex DEFAULT parameter

This specifies the name of the file where the default prefs
are held.

The format of the file is:

; comment line

  A Comment

GadgetTitle1=SettingsPrefix=DefaultValue

  Used where "SettingsPrefix=DefaultValue" is to be written

GadgetTitle2==List Values=Default Values

  Used for an MLIST where multiple switch values are to be written.

Prefixing a line with a + means that that setting will not be reset
to the default value when "Reset To Defaults" is chosen.

@node GUI
@unnumberedsec GUI parameter
@cindex GUI parameter

This specifies the name of the GUI file to be used with MPGui.library.

Parameters should be specified as #n# (n starting as 0). These should
be in the same order as the DEFAULT file.

See @@@{"Docs/MPGui.doc" Link "Docs/MPGui.doc/Main"@}.

@node PORTNAME
@unnumberedsec PORTNAME parameter
@cindex PORTNAME parameter

This specifies the name to use as an ARexx port. If not supplied then
no ARexx port is created.

See @@@{"Docs/MPGui.doc" Link "Docs/MPGui.doc/Main"@}.

